msContents.summary: Student notes from the lectures of Karl Weierstrass on analytical and elliptical functions, perhaps partly taken and compiled by Archibald Lamont Daniels, an American graduate student in mathematics at Göttingen and Berlin who later taught mathematics at the University of Vermont.

msItem.title: Einige auf die Theorie der analy?tischen Functionen mehrerer Vera?nderlichen sich beziehende Sa?tze, p. 1
Anwendungen der elliptischen Functionen auf Problems der Geometrie und Mechanik, Sommersemester 1879, p. 189
Einiges aus der Mechanik des Himmels, p. 356

supportDesc.extent: 188 leaves : 246 x 196 (205 x 156) mm. bound to 252 x 210 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Paper, i + 188 + i leaves; [1-188, 1-2], 3-164, [253-376]; contemporary foliation in ink in third work, upper outer corners.

layoutDesc.layout: Ruled paper with outer margins printed in red.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in cursive script, possibly by multiple hands.

binding.p: Quarter cloth over marbled boards, with spine title Weiestrass, Vermischtes (matches the binding of LJS 207).

history.provenance: Formerly owned by Archibald Lamont Daniels, with inscription A. L. Daniels, Berlin-Göttingen, 1879-1883, 49 Mansfield Ave., Burlington, Vt., 1910 (front flyleaf).
Formerly owned by Sydney Ross, professor of chemistry, Rensselaer Polytechnic Institute, Troy, New York (bookplate, inside upper cover).
Appears in 19th Century Shop's cat. 39, p. 23.
Formerly owned by John D. Stanitz (Cleveland, Ohio), Ms. 37.
Acquired by Lawrence J. Schoenberg with other Stanitz manuscripts, Sept. 1997.
Deposit by Lawrence J. Schoenberg and Barbara Brizdle, 2013.
